sentences: She is the first female vocalist from the UK to record an entire album in Japanese on Number One (2001) (JVC/Victor Entertainment Inc).
From the mid-1990s until 2017 Godfrey was one of Heaven 17's resident female vocalists, both in the studio and on tour.
On 21 November 2008, she made her first TV appearance with the group, on ITV's Now
She later completed the 2008 'Steel City Tour' where Heaven 17 supported The Human League.
Billie Godfrey appeared in broadband company Plusnet's national TV advertising campaign in 2010 as part of Heaven 17.
